# Docker build context excludes. Build context is the repo root for both
# apps/api and apps/workers images (monorepo-aware pnpm deploy needs the
# whole workspace + lockfile). Keep the context lean so remote Fly builds
# stay fast and no secrets/artefacts leak into an image layer.

# Dependencies — reinstalled from the frozen lockfile inside the build.
**/node_modules
.pnpm-store

# Secrets — NEVER copy .env into an image. Fly injects config via secrets
# at runtime; dotenv no-ops when the file is absent.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Build artefacts / caches
**/.next
**/dist
**/.turbo
**/storybook-static
**/coverage
**/playwright-report
**/test-results

# VCS + editor + OS cruft
.git
.gitignore
**/.DS_Store
.vscode
.idea

# Docs & deploy manifests aren't needed at runtime
docs
**/*.md

# Tests aren't needed in the runtime image (kept out of the deploy prune too)
**/test
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
